The paper deals with text classification, which is a problem in machine learning and falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The use of regularization techniques and variable selection algorithms is common in the field of machine learning, particularly in the subfield of statistical learning theory (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of textual data, which is a core area of research in computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of image features for text classification, which suggests a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of high-dimensional data, which is a common problem in data science (cs.DS).
